description: Demolition of buildings and construction of two three-storey terraces comprising 14 three-bedroom and 18 four-bedroom houses and part 4/5/6/7 storey building containing 249 flats (23 studios, 108 one-bedroom, 91 two-bedroom and 27 three-bedroom units) incorporating 63 key worker units; construction of two-storey refuse and energy centre building; provision of 271 car parking spaces, 320 cycle parking spaces; refuse storage in basement; landscaping and formation of emergency vehicle access road to Bromyard Avenue
decision_conditions: The development hereby permitted shall be begun before the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.  Reason:  In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended). | The development shall be carried out with a phasing programme to be approved of in writing by the Local Planning Authority before the development commences and each phase of the development shall not be carried out other than in accordance with this programme unless otherwise agreed by the Local Planning Authority.  Reason:To ensure a satisfactory form and sequence of development is achieved; in accordance with policies 1.10 and 4.1 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). |   Samples of the materials to be used for the external surfaces of all the buildings within the relevant phase shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before any part of the development is commenced within the relevant phase, and this condition shall apply not withstanding any indications as to these matters which have been given in the application.  The development shall be completed in accordance with the approved details and permanently retained.  Reason: To ensure a high quality appearance appropriate to the location and surroundings; in accordance with policies 1.4, 4.1 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). |   Details of the surface finishes to the hardsurfaced areas within the relevant phase shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before any part of the development is commenced within the relevant phase, and this condition shall apply notwithstanding any indications as to these matters which have been given in the application. The development shall be completed in accordance with the approved details and permanently retained.   Reason : To ensure a satisfactory and complementary finish for this development in the interests of the visual amenities and character of the locality; in accordance with policies 4.1 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment'(2004). | Details of the means of construction and the surface finish of the emergency access road; to include details of the means of construction and all underground works; shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority before any part of the development of the emergency access road is commenced, and this condition shall apply notwithstanding any indications as to these matters which have been given in the application. The development shall be completed in accordance with the approved details and permanently retained.  Reason : To ensure the form of construction and surface finish of the emergency access road is compatible with its restricted use for `emergency purposes` only; does not prejudice the health and stability of the existing trees and maintains the character and appearance of the grassed amenity area at the front of the site;; in accordance with policies 4.1, 4.5 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment'(2004). |   No development shall take place until there has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority drawings indicating the position, design, materials and type of boundary enclosure(s) to be erected around the full perimeter of the site and between and demarcating the boundaries of the properties within the site; including any internal fences, walls and railings on the roof terraces and around the play areas. The boundary enclosures shall be erected within each relevant phase in accordance with the approved details prior to the occupation of the units within the relevant phase and permanently retained thereafter.      Reason: To ensure a satisfactory appearance and setting for the development in the interests of the character and appearance of the area and the living conditions of future residents and occupiers of neighbouring properties; in accordance with policies 4.1 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Details of the planting within the soft landscaped areas shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of the development within the relevant phase and the approved planting shall be completed prior to the first planting season following the completion of the development, or such other time as may be agreed in writing with the Local Planning Authority. Any trees or plants which, within 5 years of planting, die, are removed or become seriously damaged or diseased shall be replaced in the next planting season with others of the same size and species and in the same locations unless otherwise approved in writing with the Local Planning Authority. This condition applies notwithstanding the indications as to these matters contained in the application.  Reason: To ensure a satisfactory landscaped appearance and green setting for this development and to ensure that the communal amenity areas are  landscaped in a manner which maximises their visual character and appearance for the residents; in accordance with adopted policies 4.1, 4.5 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Prior to the occupation of the development a schedule of landscape maintenance for a minimum period of 5 years shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The schedule shall include details for the arrangement of its implementation. The landscape maintenance shall be carried out only In accordance with the approved schedule.   Reason: To protect the landscaping in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area; in accordance adopted policies 4.1, 4.5 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | The trees numbered T1, T3, T4 and T5 shall be retained unless otherwise approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. In the event that the Local Planning Authority considers that the health, stability, safety or amenity value of these trees is unreasonably compromised by the development, then these trees shall be replaced with appropriate replacement trees (number 5) of a size, species and in a position as approved by the Local Planning Authority. Any replacement trees shall be planted within 3 months of the removal of any of the four preserved trees (T1, T3 T4 and T5).  Reason: To ensure the long term presence of trees along the frontage, in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area; in accordance adopted policies 4.1, 4.5 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004) and Supplementary Planning Guidance 9 'Trees and Development Guidelines' |  No development (including demolition works) shall take place until details of the measures proposed to protect the preserved trees (T1, T3, T4 and T5) on the site during demolition and construction works, within the relevant phase, in accordance with BS5837:2005, have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Such measures as approved shall be carried out before any works commence and shall be retained during the course of the development, unless replacement trees are agreed with the Local Planning Authority under the terms of Condition 9. This condition applies notwithstanding the details submitted with the application.     Reason:  To ensure that the preserved trees are adequately protected from damage during the course of the development; in accordance with policies 4.1 and 4.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004), and Supplementary Planning Guidance 9 'Trees and Development Guidelines'.		 | The entire root system of trees to be retained, as shown on the approved drawings, indicated by the spread of their branches, shall be protected by stout exclusion fencing until completion of the development.  Reason: To prevent damage to the trees in the interest of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with policies 4.1 and 4.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004), and Supplementary Planning Guid0ance 9 'Trees and Development Guidelines'. | The area beneath the spread of the branches of the trees to be retained as shown on the approved drawings shall not be used for the storage of building materials, plant, machinery or other items, or for vehicular access or for the burning of materials of any kind.  Reason: To prevent damage to the trees in the interest of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with policies 4.1 and 4.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004), and Supplementary Planning Guidance 9 'Trees and Development Guidelines'. | "No works or development; including any preliminary works or construction work, or storage of materials or structures, or excavations or the provision of any means of access (other than for the construction of the emergency access road) shall take place on any part of the site frontage with Bromyard Avenue, defined as all the land within the site located west of the building line of the apartment building and northern terrace of houses; unless otherwise approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Before the development commences, the said land shall be fully enclosed and protected until practical completion of the development, in accordance with details to be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  Reason: To safeguard the land at the front of the site in the interests of the future health and amenity of the trees and in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area in accordance with policies 4.1 and 4.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004), and Supplementary Planning Guidance 9 'Trees and Development Guidelines. | No development shall take place until details of servicing (the arrangements for deliveries and removals) and refuse and recycling collection arrangements have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The approved arrangements shall be implemented prior to first occupation of any of the units hereby approved, and permanently retained thereafter. This condition applies notwithstanding the details submitted with the application  Reason: To ensure suitable loading, unloading and refuse collection arrangements are provided in order to ensure pedestrian and highway safety and to protect the living conditions of occupants of nearby properties, in accordance with policies 2.10 and 9.1 of adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Notwithstanding the information shown on the submitted plans, details of refuse storage and waste management (including provision for recycling) within the relevant phase in accordance with adopted standards, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.  Such provision shall be implemented as approved prior to first occupation of the relevant phase of the development and retained permanently.This condition applies notwithstanding the details submitted with the application.  Reason: To protect the living and working conditions of occupiers of the development and to meet the Council's sustainability policies, in accordance with policy 2.10 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). | "The car parking spaces serving the relevant phase of the development, including the disabled spaces, and the associated access and manoeuvring space hereby permitted (as shown on the approved drawings) shall be surfaced and available for use prior to first occupation of units in the relevant phase and thereafter shall not be obstructed or used for any other purpose except with the prior permission of the local planning authority obtained through the submission of a planning application. All parking shall be for use of the residents of the development and their visitors and for no other purpose."  Reason: To ensure adequate parking is provided and retained within the site in the interests of the amenities of the occupiers of the surrounding properties and in the interests of general highway safety and the free flow of traffic within the site and on the local highway, in accordance with policies 4.3 and 9.1 in the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 2004 'Plan for the Environment'. | Prior to the first occupation of any of the residential units within the development full details of the distribution, allocation and management of all the car parking spaces on the site for use by the occupiers of the market housing and affordable units shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details of the distribution and management of the car parking as approved shall be implemented prior to the first occupation of any part of the development permitted and  thereafter permanently retained. This condition applies notwithstanding the information contained in the submitted application.  Reason:To ensure that there is an acceptable distribution of parking spaces for all occupiers of the new development in accordance with policies 4.3, 5.5  and 9.1 in the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 2004 'Plan for the Environment'. | The on-site vehicle speed limit shall be no more than 10 mph; and details of the traffic management measures to be operated within the site, including the timing of their implementation, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to commencement of works within each relevant phase and shall be implemented only in accordance with the approved details and timing, and thereafter permanently retained.  Reason: In the interests of pedestrian safety in accordance with policies 9.5 and 9.1 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 2004 'Plan for the Environment' | "The cycle parking spaces a shown on the approved drawings shall be provided for the relevant phase of the development prior to first occupation of the units on the relevant phase, and thereafter shall be permanently retained and kept continuously available for cycle parking and shall not be used for any other purpose. All cycle parking shall be for the use of residents of the development and their visitors and for not other purpose."  Reason: To ensure that adequate cycle parking is available within the site in accordance with policy 9.6 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). |   The emergency access to Bromyard Avenue, as shown on the approved drawing shall be used solely as a means of access in the case of an emergency and shall not be used for any other purpose, including access for the purposes of the demolition of the existing buildings and construction of the new development; nor for refuse collections, deliveries or for any other servicing purposes, unless otherwise approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.      Reason: The unrestricted general use of this access, by reason of its location and juxtaposition with other junctions, would unacceptably prejudice the free flow and safety of traffic along Bromyard Avenue; in accordance with policy 9.1 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). | All residential units hereby approved shall be constructed to `Lifetime Homes Standards`, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority. Details to demonstrate compliance with these standards shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and shall be implemented as approved prior to first occupation of each dwelling. This condition applies notwithstanding the details submitted with the application.  Reason: To ensure access for all for future occupiers in accordance with policies 4.1 and 5.3 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). |   No less than 10% of all the dwellings within the development, to include a mix of houses and flats of varying size, shall be constructed so as to be 'wheelchair accessible'. Details of the units, their size location and layout within the relevant phase shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to first occupation of the specified units within the relevant phase and permanently retained thereafter.  Reason: To ensure suitable accommodation for disabled persons, in accordance with policies 4.1 and 5.3 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Prior to the commencement of development within the relevant phase, details shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, for any mitigation works to protect sensitive rooms within that phase from external noise and vibration and sensitive rooms from internal building services noise. The works, as approved, shall be completed before occupation of any part of the building in the relevant phase and thereafter permanently retained.  Reason: To protect the living conditions of occupiers of the development hereby approved, in accordance with policies 4.11 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Before the development is commenced, a detailed site investigation shall be carried out by a competent person to establish the extent, degree and nature of any site contamination. The method and extent of the site investigation shall be agreed with the Local Planning Authority prior to commencement of any work. A written method statement for the remediation of the land and/or groundwater contamination affecting the site shall be agreed in writing with the Local Planning Authority prior to commencement and all requirements shall be implemented and completed to the satisfaction of the local planning authority by a competent person. No deviation from this scheme shall be made without the express written permission of the Local Planning Authority. Copies of a completion report confirming the objectives, methods, results and conclusions of the remediation works have been complied with shall be submitted to the Local Planning Authority.  Reason: To ensure that the ground conditions are safe, in the interests of the amenities of future occupiers of the site; in accordance with policy 2.7 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 2004 'Plan for the Environment'. | Details of the layout, surfacing and equipment within the children's play area shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority prior to the commencement of the development hereby permitted and the approved details shall be completed prior to the first occupation of the 120th dwelling and thereafter these facilities shall not be removed except with the prior permission of the Local Planning Authority obtained through the submission of a planning application.   Reason: To ensure an appropriate Childs Play Area is provided within the development in accordance with policies 3.5 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). ) and Supplementary Planning Guidance `13` Garden Space`. |   Details of the laying out, landscaping and balustrades for the roof top amenity areas in the relevant phase and measures to prevent overlooking of surrounding residential properties shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of the development within the relevant phase and the detail so approved shall be completed prior to the first occupation of any of the units within the relevant phase with access to the amenity areas and these arrangements shall not thereafter be altered except with the prior written permission of the Local Planning Authority obtained through the submission of a planning application. This condition applies to the apartment block and the townhouses within the northern terrace.  Reason : In the interests of the visual amenities of the locality and to safeguard the amenities of occupiers of surrounding properties in accordance with policies 4.1, 4.5 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Pan 2004 'Plan for the Environment'. | Any fixtures, furniture, landscaping, plants and other similar features proposed to be installed on the communal roof top garden areas and private balconies must be permanently secured. No hanging of washing shall occur on any of the balconies.  Reason: In the interests of the visual amenity of the area and community safety in accordance with policies 4.1 and 4.4 of the  adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Details of the design of a barrier or screen to prevent the overlooking of adjoining residentail properties in Ashfield Road from the roof terraces on the northern terrace of houses shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details shall include the height, position and external apperance of the barrier(s) and shall also include section drawings indicating the lines of sight between the roof terraces and adjoining residential properties in Ashfield Road. The barriers as approved shall be erected prior to first occupation of any of the town houses in the northern terrace and thereafter permanently retained. This condition applies notwithstanding any indications as to this matter in the submitted application.  Reason: To protect the living conditions of adjoining residential occupiers in accordance with policies 4.1 and 5.5 of the  adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | The communal garden areas as shown on the approved plans shall be permanently retained for the communal use of all the residents of the development. No walls or fences or other means of enclosure, other than those shown on the approved drawings, shall be erected within or around these garden areas, unless otherwise approved by the Local Planning Authority, and thereafter carried out as approved.  Reason: To ensure that all residents have access to some outdoor amenity space; to ensure a uniform design and appearance is retained and and in order to secure a safe environment in accordance with policies 4.1, 4.5 and 5.5 of the  adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning General Permitted Development Order 1995 (or any Order revoking and re-enacting that Order with or without modification), no extensions, enlargement or external alterations shall be carried out to any of the houses within the development, unless otherwise approved by the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.  Reason: To maintain the design integrity of the development and to ensure sufficient private amenity space is retained for the dwellings; in accordance with accordance with policies 4.1 and 5.5 of the  adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Details of site drainage shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the commencement of the development and the development shall be carried out only in accordance with the approved details.   Reason: To ensure satisfactory drainage is provided in the interests of the water environment and without damage to preserved trees on the site; in accordance with policies 2.5 and 4.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 2004 'Plan for the Environment'. | No development approved by this permission shall be commenced until a scheme for the provision and implementation of surface water run-off limitation by means of a sustainable drainage system shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The scheme shall be implemented in accordance with the approved programme and details. The surface water runoff rates shall be established by calculations for the proposed and existing development.  Reason: To prevent the increased risk of flooding and improve water quality; in accordance with policy 2.5 in the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 2004 'Plan for the Environment'. | Surface water source control measures shall be taken in accordance with details to be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. Such measures approved shall be implemented before the development is occupied and permanently retained.  Reason: To prevent the increased risk of flooding and improve water quality; in accordance with policy 2.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 2004 'Plan for the Environment'. |   Details of any external lighting to be installed within the site or on any part of the buildings within the relevant phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to the development commencing within the relevant phase. Such details should demonstrate that the recommendations of the Institute of Lighting Engineers made in its Guidance Notes for the Reduction of Light Pollution will be met Any external lighting approved shall be installed and maintained in accordance with the aforementioned approved standards.   Reason: To protect the living conditions of occupiers of the area; in accordance with  policies 4.1 and 4.12 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). | The 63 units of affordable accommodation hereby approved shall be permanently retained on site and shall not be used for any other purpose, including private tenure, without the prior written approval of the Local Planning Authority.  Reason: To ensure that an acceptable amount of affordable housing is maintained within the development; in accordance with policy 5.2 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Details of crime prevention and security measures for the buildings, footways and cycle ways, car parking and cycle parking areas, and communal gardens at ground level within the relevant phase: (including (i) access controls to the car park and entrance doors (ii) lighting within the site, including in the underground parking areas and pedestrain routes, and  (iii) CCTV coverage), shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to commencement of development within the relevant phase. The approved details shall be implemented before the first occupation of any part of the development within the relevant phase, and shall be permanently retained.  .Reason:  In the interests of the safety of residents and visitors; in accordance with policies 4.3 and 4.4 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004), and Supplementary Planning Guidance SPG 8 'Safer Ealing'. |   Notwithstanding the information provided with the application, details of measures to provide 10 per cent of the energy requirements of the development as renewable energy shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to commencement of development.  The approved details shall be implemented in accordance with the approved energy strategy and phasing plan prior to first occupation of any of the residential units within the apartment building with each relevant phase and thereafter permanently retained.  Reason: To ensure the proposal contributes to its energy requirements in accordance with policy 2.9 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Prior to the commencement of the development, including commencement of any demolition and site clearance works, a `Demolition and Construction Strategy` shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The means of demolition and site clearance and construction shall be carried out only in accordance with the approved Strategy, which should also include details of the means of access for demolition and construction works and details of noise, vibration and dust mitigation measures during the redevelopment.  Reason: To protect the living conditions of nearby occupiers, in accordance with policies 4.11 and 5.5 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). | Arrangements shall be put in place throughout the duration of the building works to clean the wheels of vehicles leaving the site and to ensure the security of any loads being removed from the site. These measures shall be put into effect on each vehicle leaving the site.  Reason: To prevent the spread of mud, dirt and debris on the adjoining roads, in the interests of highway safety in accordance with policy 4.1 of the Council's adopted UDP 'Plan for the Environment' (2004). |   The windows in the south elevations of apartments in the +finger+ elements of the apartment building shall be obscure-glazed before their first occupation of the building and thereafter permanently retained in such condition.   Reason: To safeguard the privacy of residents of residential units in Bromyard House adjacent; in accordance with  policies 4.1 and 4.12 of the adopted Ealing Unitary Development Plan, 'New Plan for the Environment' (2004).
